  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Malaria Control in Mbale</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Malaria is the most common cause of illness and death in both children and adults in Mbale, Uganda. When detected early, malaria can be treated with effective malaria medicines that are now generally available for free in public sector health facilities. However, if left too late, malaria soon becomes life threatening, especially for children. The aim of this project is to help these children survive. The project will build the skills of health workers and improve the quality of the services people receive. They will ensure that children with danger signs of severe malaria are immediately referred to the right place and treated by staff with the necessary equipment, supplies, knowledge and skills. They will also work with families to make sure those children with danger signs are taken immediately to a higher-level health facility or hospital. As a result of the project, the number of malaria-related deaths of children under five in health facilities will be reduced.</narrative>
  </description>
